/-- Geometric-sector source for the selected raw-orbit `faceSucc` transition.

Given a sharp boundary-free local angular source, this row says that the
geometric `faceSucc` head of each selected frontier iterate lies in the open
angular sector determined by the two selected local frontier heads at the
successor tail.  The reducer below turns this sector fact into the concrete
